Text:
Billions in customer assets are missing after FTX's collapse. Sam Bankman-Fried said publicly that FTX customer funds were improperly transferred to Alameda’s bank accounts.
 
@silvergatebank's response is inadequate — the bank must answer for its role.
https://t.co/kGL8lCYAfR

FTX’s collapse should be a wake-up call. @SECGov,
@TheJusticeDept &amp; @USTreasury should use their expansive authority to crack down hard on crypto fraud. Congress must close loopholes &amp; back up these financial cops on the beat with more resources.

My oped: https://t.co/ARdtun2pAb

The Biden admin is trying to stop a merger handing 75% of the southeast sugar market to two firms, but a top @USDA economist testified against @TheJusticeDept — raising ethics concerns and likely increasing consumer prices.

@SenBooker and I want answers.
https://t.co/NqKNXzyAVN

New relief from the Biden administration to help working families, reducing utility bills immediately and cutting energy costs long-term.

@VP Harris’ announcement is welcome news for families in Massachusetts and an important step to help lower costs. 
https://t.co/P5FgF1oO42

Big Oil companies' record profits are a windfall of war and this profiteering has got to stop.

@POTUS is right: Congress should consider a windfall profits tax and provide Americans with relief at the gas pump.

@SenWhitehouse and I have a bill to do just that.

Fantastic visit in Boston and Brockton helping people sign up for student debt relief. Apply here! https://t.co/jbxJMCKnFl
 
@POTUS is delivering life-changing relief for millions of working people.

Next stops: Worcester and Springfield. https://t.co/CbslEAZTW5

Democrats beat Big Pharma and will lower the costs of prescription drugs with the Inflation Reduction Act. 

@SecBecerra should build on this progress and crack down on Big Pharma's monopoly power.
https://t.co/zxU047Nrd5

Semiconductor funding should be used to support US manufacturing &amp; strengthen supply chains—not line the pockets of CEOs with stock buybacks.

@SecRaimondo’s responsible for implementing strong taxpayer protections. My colleagues &amp; I will ensure she does. 
https://t.co/QzVeTOj4uM

100 days since the Supreme Court stripped away the right to abortion, Republican politicians are jeopardizing the lives of millions of women.

@POTUS is taking important action to protect reproductive care. Congress needs to make Roe the law nationwide.
https://t.co/OT0hn5G7Cy

These resources will save lives and support people in recovery.

I've long called for greater investment to address the substance use epidemic and held the Trump admin accountable for failing to take real action.

@POTUS is keeping his promise. We can beat the opioid crisis.

I've worked my entire career for a more fair bankruptcy system—and I won't stop pushing for action.
 
@POTUS's plan to cancel student debt will help millions of hard working people, but @TheJusticeDept must update its policy on student bankruptcy relief.
https://t.co/jd7sR70lNJ

Credit card companies like @Visa, @Mastercard, and @AmericanExpress can and should do more to help stop mass shootings.

@RepDean and I are urging these companies to step up and help identify suspicious purchases to prevent gun violence.
https://t.co/kkqsYxpmzd

A HISTORIC day for Americans:
@US_FDA announced that it will allow people with mild to moderate hearing loss to buy safe and affordable hearing aids right off the shelf! I’ve been fighting for this for 5+ years and this is a terrific win for consumers.
https://t.co/GGyYMXqZV8

.@Equifax inaccurately reported consumers' credit scores, causing rejections or higher rates for car loans, mortgage, &amp; credit card applicants.  Equifax still hasn’t fully come clean. This is scandalous.
 
@MarkWarner, @CongressmanRaja, and I want answers.
https://t.co/A6uheoktrb

Now that this extremist Supreme Court overturned #RoeVWade, there's more urgency than ever to expand access to medication abortion. 

@SenatorBaldwin, @maziehirono and I outlined seven options that the Biden Admin can take to have the greatest impact.
https://t.co/R5ntIMrmuJ

Canceling student loan debt:
 
Would help close the racial wealth gap among borrowers, change the lives of workers across the country, and create a brighter future for millions of Americans.
 
@POTUS, it’s time to get this done.

The Supreme Court’s reckless decision to overturn Roe has endangered millions of Americans. 

@POTUS and @SecBecerra should declare national and public health emergencies to unlock powerful authorities to protect access to abortion care:
https://t.co/H7qwnJsUEa

The Supreme Court overturned Roe, unleashing Republican state legislatures to ban abortions &amp; forcing doctors to withhold lifesaving care.
 
@POTUS &amp; @SecBecerra should issue emergency declarations to unlock critical authorities to protect abortion access.
https://t.co/H7qwnJKvvI

.@AFTunion President @rweingarten is right: student debt cancellation “is the only just and moral response to the nation’s student debt crisis, directly combating the enormous economic challenges faced by working people."

@POTUS should #CancelStudentDebt.
https://t.co/Ivy88pVFfq

Democrats must use every tool to protect the constitutional right to an abortion. 

@PattyMurray and I are leading over 20 Senators urging @POTUS to use his executive authority to defend reproductive freedoms from this extremist Supreme Court.
https://t.co/NHn1yniRcW

Private equity has been buying up everything from homes to hospitals — hurting families and workers, and potentially breaking U.S. laws.

@JusticeATR is right to enforce our antitrust laws to promote competitive markets and lower consumer prices.
https://t.co/tHonYnhUHq

.@JPMorgan, @BankofAmerica, &amp; @WellsFargo pad their pockets with billions from overdraft fees, which target the lowest-income Americans. 

@SenBooker, @RepMaloney, &amp; I are calling on them to stop charging these fees immediately. 
https://t.co/Sl9vpLl94o

Right now, Russian oligarchs and criminals can secretly stash their assets in U.S. private equity firms and hedge funds. 

@SenWhitehouse and I are calling on @USTreasury and @SECGov to close this loophole.
https://t.co/xMZSexICSx

Water is a human right and Wall Street shouldn't be allowed to exploit it for profit. 

@RepRoKhanna and I introduced a bill to protect water from Wall Street speculation and ensure this essential resource isn't auctioned off to the highest bidder.
https://t.co/stJXcIMF0Y

About 40% of people with student loan debt don’t have a college diploma. 

Many students enroll in college with hope of a degree and a better job, but then life gets in the way and they’re left with mountains of debt. 

@POTUS should #CancelStudentDebt.

Big banks have been snatching money away from families to pad their profits by charging overdraft fees.
 
@Citi just committed to eliminating this abusive practice. Now, other giant banks like @jpmorgan should do the same.
https://t.co/dLRkie2sdY

Student debt is a racial justice issue.

After 20 years of payments, the typical Black borrower owes 95% of their initial student loan, yet the typical white borrower owes 6%.

@POTUS can help close the racial wealth gap by canceling student debt.

We have a student debt crisis in America. 

Student debt is holding back working people from starting their own businesses, saving for their first home &amp; investing in their families’ future.

@POTUS should #CancelStudentDebt to strengthen our economy &amp; build out the middle-class.

.@WellsFargo has been caught rigging the arbitration process to escape accountability for hurting investors, and @FINRA let them. 

@RepKatiePorter and I want answers about the bank’s atrocious behavior and FINRA's inability to police the financial system.
https://t.co/Tg3LN6zJwZ

Because of @usedgov's changes to the broken Public Service Loan Forgiveness program, thousands of public servants are finally getting their student loans forgiven.

@POTUS should permanently #CancelStudentDebt for all borrowers. It's the right thing to do.
https://t.co/lOQPuzdvZE

Half of federal student loan borrowers are at risk of falling behind if payments resume in May.

@POTUS can prevent this from happening—it’s time to #CancelStudentDebt.
https://t.co/3hR8t91f4i

For years, big banks and financial companies have gotten away with exploiting consumers with overdraft and other junk fees to fatten their profits. 

@SenBooker and I introduced a bill to end these predatory practices and I'm glad @CFPB is taking action.
https://t.co/xo0WpkAz4v

For many first-generation students, a college degree symbolizes the American Dream—but too often these dreams are crushed by debt. The average Latino borrower still owes 83% of loans 12 yrs after starting college. 

@POTUS must #CancelStudentDebt.
https://t.co/cMveHyNw5p

The pause on student loan payments has helped borrowers pay off other forms of debt, given people economic freedom, and allowed many to pursue new job opportunities. 

@POTUS should permanently #CancelStudentDebt.
https://t.co/b4GU4U0O3o

The student loan payment pause has helped borrowers make ends meet throughout the pandemic.

@POTUS should #CancelStudentDebt to jumpstart our economy and give millions of people permanent relief.
https://t.co/jQmEMLdQKu

The stepped-up basis loophole lets the wealthiest Americans inherit fortunes without paying a penny in capital gains tax—a massive subsidy that perpetuates the racial wealth gap and inequality.

@DorothyABrown is right: we need to close this loophole.
https://t.co/PVMlbMBYLv
